title.narrative: UK support to enable effective and accountable rapid medical and search and rescue response during humanitarian emergencies.

description.narrative: This activity (UK support to enable effective and accountable rapid medical and search and rescue response during humanitarian emergencies.) is a component of Emergency Deployment Team (EDT) Programme reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Humanitarian assistance' and a budget of £21,317,027. This component benefits Developing countries, unspecified, and works in the following sector(s): Material relief assistance and services . , with the following implementing partners: Crown Agents Limited, DAI Europe, Handicap International (UK), Merseyside Fire and Rescue Authority, Palladium International Ltd (UK), UK-Med. The start date is 07-09-2011 and the end date is 31-07-2022.
